Trifolium hybridum

   [10533.jpg]
   Authority L.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Fabales:Leguminosae
   Synonyms T. elegans Savi (ssp. elegans), Amoria hybrida
   Common names alsike clover, hybrid clover, Swedish clover, Alsatian
   clover, trefle de Suede, trefle hybride, Schwedenklee, trifoglio
   ibrido, alsike-kløver, smuk kløver, alsikekløver, alsikeapila,
   túnsmári, trevo hibrido, trevo da Suecia, trebol hibrido, trebol sueco,
   alsikeklöver, Trifolii albi et rubri flos
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 10533

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A semierect, short-crowned legume. Flowers vary from
   white to rose-colored. USES Grown as a forage and hay crop. KILLING T
   Frost resistant. GROWING PERIOD Perennial, often grown as an annual or
   biennial. In the United States, it is usually sown in early spring, can
   be grassed in June-July, and harvested for seeds in August. It is
   harvested for hay while in bloom. Flowers and fruit from May-September.
   COMMON NAMES Alsike clover, Swedish clover, Hybrid clover. FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonyms: T. fistulosum, T. michelianum. Alsike clover is
   native of northern Europe and it is adapted to cool climates.

   Sources
